{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_icaria_ver01/data/sn86090330/00517175201/1908060701/0792.xml":{"full_text":"(AIKDOME. Big Tent Theater.)\nSunday Night, June 7. Miss Ina Lehr and Dramatic Comoany, Four-Act\n\u2022\u2022SEX AGAINST SEX\u201d Drama 10c\u2014ADMISSION\u201410.\nELECTRIC PARK\nV ADMISSION FREE\nBand Concerts Daily at 6 p. m. and\nSunday 4 p. m.\nREFINED VAUDEVILLE\nTwo performances every evening\n9:15. Prices, children 10c,\nadults 20c. Reserved Seats 10c ex\ntra,\nSUNDAY, JUNE 7\nMARVO, THE JAIL BREAKER\n(New Program Each Night)\nz\nPROFESSOR McLAINE'S FAMILY\nOF TRAINED DOGS\nNEWTON C. BASSETT\nExquisite Baritone Singer\nEARL AND ANNIE MeLAINE\nIn Their Sensational Flying Acts\nELECTROSCOPE\nLatest Moving Pictures. (Three\nChanges of Program Weekly)\n20\u2014CONCESSIONS\u201420\nIn Full Swing.\nSAN ANTONIO\u2019S\nGREAT CHAUTAUQUA\nBox Office Now Open at Grand\nOpera House.\nFirst Perfrmance at Electric Park\nFriday Night, June 12.\nI 9 PERFORMARCES I 9\nAdmission 25c, 50c. 75c and $l.OO\nSer, son Tickets $2.50\nUnited States Senator Bob Taylor,\nFrederick Warde, United States Sena\ntor Berry, George Bain and others on\nprogram.\nTurner Carnival\nT onight\nGates Open 7 P. M.\nlOc\u2014 LYRIC\u2014 10c\nVAUDEVILLE\n5--BIG ACTS--5\nNEW BILL TONIGHT\nBASE BALL\nSAN ANTONIO\nvs.\nGALVESTON\nTODAY\nGame Called at 4 o\u2019clock\nMonday 5 o'clock,\nBASE BALL\nCJTY LEAGUE\nDOUBLE-HEADER\nKRISCH PARK.\nSarnes Called at 2:30 and 4:15 p. m.\nADMITTANCE 15c. LADIES FREE.\nTake West End Car.\nMOVING PICTURE THEATHSE\nPALACE MOVING\nPICTURE SHOW\n\"WORKMAN'S REVENGE.\"\n105 West Houston StreeL\nADMISSION sc.\nPta Picture Show\nALAMO PLAZA.\n\u201cBURNING OF ROME.\"\n5c ..ADMISSION\u2014 5c\nAMUSE MENTS.\n\"A DOLLAR SHOW FOR A DIME.\u201d\nBoth Phones.\ni BATES CO.\nk Agent.\n3 We RENT all\n\u2022o\u00bb makes of\nThe machine you TYPEWRITERS\nwill eventually nrLWnilLnj\nbuy. 311 Navarro St.\n\u201cNOW OPEN\u201d\nMISSION CAFE\nThe Handsomest Short Order Cafe In\nthe City.\nFine Chill and Good Coffee,\na Specialty.\n808 East Houston. Opposite Moore Bldg.\nScheuermeyer\u2019s I\n==Park= I\nCOOL \u00ab\u00ab0 riESSMT B\nDiazSlsters\u2019Orchesira I\nElegant Kitchen and EH\nBest of Service. M\nTAKE HOT WELLS CAR H\nTCUnu\nSoft Shell Turtle Soup\nConsomme Printaniere\nTrout. White Wine Sauce\nShoe String Potatoes\nCalf\u2019s Head- en Tortue\nItcast Young Turkey\nCranberry Sauce\nNew Boiled Potatoes in Cream\nString Beans\nCorn on Cob Cucumber Salad\nCherry Ice Assorted Cake\nRoquefort Cheese\nBent\u2019s Water Crackers\nCafe Noir\nJune 7. 1908. Price 50 Cents.\n((city' NEWS J\n$55,015 in New Buildings.\nFor the week ending yesterday Jo\nseph Wahrenburger. city building in\nspector. issued permits for $55,015\nwot th of new buildings in San An\ntonio, including 42 new residences\nWith but few exceptions the new\ndwellings are of the four and five-room\ncottage type and are scattered\nthroughout the outlying districts.\no\nImproving the Plaza.\nStreet commissioner Russi yesterday\nstarted a force of men at work making\nrepairs on Main plaza, the work being\nbetween West Commerce and Dolorosa\nstreets. A large section of the old\nmesquite block pavement has been\ntorn up and the improved \u201cCallaghan\u201d\nmethod of paving substituted. The\nsuccess of the macadamized streets\nstarted a few weeks since by the\ni CHAPA'S ANNEX.\nI take pleasure tn announcing to\n4 the people of San Antonio that I 7\nhave opened next to my drug store\nan Ice cream parlor second to none\nIn the south. The fountain Is the T\nrichest In Texas, made In Texa* T\nbv Texans and for Texans.\nF. A. CHAPA.\nDR. IH. TERRILL\nSPECIALIST\nChronic Diseases of Men and Women.\nConroy Bldg. Alamo Plaza.\n\u2014Office Hours\nBto 12 a. m. 1 to 8:30 p. m.\nMISS FRIEDA ENGELHARDT\nLadles\u2019 Hairdresser and Wigmaker.\nShampooing parlor. Manicuring\nand face massage. Scalp treatment.\nManufacturer of hair goods.\nWe rent wigs for ball* and parties.\nTerretl Bldg. 212 Ave. O.\nNew phono 1003. E. L. Francois, Mgr\nU ;\u2014rr.\u201c.. ss\u2014\nI Art Stained Glass I\nMirrors, Plate Glass, etc.\nOld Mirrors Reslivered.\nL. M. SAMUELS,\nOld phon* 2873. 303 Main Ave. I\nL. T. WATERS UNDERTAKING CO\nEmbalmer*. Funeral Director*.\nException*! Shipping FaoiUUe*. Priests\n\nSUNDAY, JUNE 7, 1908. THE SAN ANTONIO LIGHT Sunday, june 7, 1908.\nECZEMA CURED.\nNice, Clean Liquid Does the Work.\n\u2019The public Is now able to secure\nan absolutely harmless rqfnedy for the\ncure of skin diseases. Eczema Is the\nitching disease that Dearly distracts\none. Who is there that has ever hen\nthis tv rrlble disease that would not\ngive anything they possessed to be\ncured?\nDr. R. Atkinson, physician and sur\ngeon. San Marcos. Texas, writ\u2019s to\nihe imperia'. Medical Co.; I have no\nsrtt of objection to you publishing the\nletter I wrote you last. While it was\nnot written for publication, I only\nstated therein plain facts, which you\nare at liberty to use in any way you\nmay desire. My wife was cured by\nyour Imperial Remedy, and she has\nhad no return of the trouble.\nThousands of people throughout Tex\nas and the South have been perma\nnently cured by Imperial Remedy. For\ntwenty-five years Imperial Remedy\nhas beer used in nearly every city,\nvillage and hamlet in the South for\nthe cure of skin diseases. Its purity is\nguaranteed. If you are a sufferer, h\nsure cure awaits you. Nearly all drug\ngists sell Imperial Remedy, but in\nease you do not find it for sale at\nyour nearest drug store it will be sent\nfrom our laboratory to any part of the\nUnited States, express prepaid, for\nSI.W per bottle. Imperial Medicine\nCo. Houston, Texas.\nmayor as an experiment, has led to\nmuch of the repair work being done\nwith the same material. The natural\ncement-limestope after being pulver\nizwi bv means of a heavy steam roller\nIs oiled and provides a perfect road\nbed.\nGoes on Visit to lowa.\nG. W. Merritt, for five years first\nsergeant of F troop, First cavalry\nstationed both in the Philippine\nIslands and at Fort Sam Houston, but\nfor the past year with the San Antonio\nTraction company, is off on a month\u2019s\nleav< of absence and has gone to his\nold home in lowa to visit his parents\nand relatives whom he has not seen\nfor eight year\u00bb.\nCertificates of Title.\nSuburban lots are often bought\nwithout examination of the title,\nbecause the abstract costs more than\nthe property will stand. This is a dan\ngerous practice.\nFor a small fee I will have the title\nto such property examined and issue a\ncertificate of title thereto. Such cer\ntificates show who owns the property,\nall liens, defects and taxes due, and\ncarry my $2OO guarantee that they\nare correct.\nBEN A. STRIBLING.\nManager of the Bexar Abstract Co..\n209 W. Commerce street.\nNewnam Is Home.\nDetective Frank Newnam, of the lo\ncal police force, returned yesterday\nafter a two weeks\u2019 vacation which he\nspent on a trip to the principal cities\nof the south and Atlantic states. Mr.\nNewnam went as far north as Norfolk.\nVa., and says that while he had an\nenjoyable trip he did not see anything\nthat made him sorry that he lived in\nTexas and San Antonio.\nSells Bungalow.\nThe record of sales made by the E.\nA. Fox Co., shows a transfer to D.\nO. C. Daugherty, of Louisville. Ky.. of\na five-room bungalow in Villa Rosa\nfor which the consideration was\n$2900. Two lots were also sold to\nJ. E. King, of Huntsville, and Miss\nClifton and C. D. Newton were a,so\nthe purchasers of lots.\no\nWill Introduce State Books.\nIt was stated yesterday afternoon\nby Superintendent C J. Lukin that all\nthe books recommended by the text\nbook board would be introduced into\nthe schools, except those published\nby the American Text Book company\nand allied companies which are under\nthe ban of the state which makes\ntrust allegations.\nSuperintendent Lukin is expecting\nadvices from the attorney-general in\nregard to the matter within the next\nfew days.\nHot Weather Troubles of\nthe Over-fat\nThe worst is that \u2019\u2019\u25a0mothering\u201d sensa\ntion. This la so suggestive of apoplexy,\nlast rites and undertaker* that It gets on\none\u2019s nerves.\nWhen this worriment Is added to the\nother hot weather troubles of the overfat,\nthe question of reducing get* some seriou*\nconsideration. Fat folks begin about like\nthis: \u201cExercise overtaxes the heart\u2014diet\ning (especially dieting the liquids) Is Im\npossible\u2014and the so-called remedies usu\nally ruin the stomach. To adopt any one\nof these would simply add to my present\ndistress That Is the way most fat folks\nreason. Nothing comes of It.\nStill relief from one's tush trou\nbles can be gained only by reducing. But\nh Well here is the information desired\u2014\nand it Is \"straight\u201d Information, too. Do\nyou want to reduce a pound a day\u2014with\nout exercising, dieting, stomach distress,\nor the foftn.ition of wrinkles? Nothing\neasier believe It or not. Simply ask your\ndruggist (or write the Marniola Co., De\ntroit) for a eevcnty-llve-cent case of Mar\nmols Prescription Tablets.\nHe will give you enough tablets for that\namount to last quite a while. Take them\nas he directs daily and you will soon are\nthe fat begin to slip off. Then continue\nuntil you are as shin as you want to be.\nThat's all. There Is no harm In them\n(thev are made Identically in accordance\nwith the famous Marmols Prescription)\nan>l they cost less by a half than any\nother remedy you could get.\nEAT WATERMELONS\nand Keep Healthy\nTell Your Grocer to Order from Us.\nWe Have the BEST.\nCars On S. A. A, P. Track\nR. A. GRANT, Jr.\nG. L. TAFT\nWholesale Only\nMilitary Haza Naw Phone 648\nr\n\u2014l~\u2014>\nI\nBig Tent Theater Airdome.\nOt tlfe Ina Lehr Dramatic company\nwhich opens the Big Tent Theater\ntomorrow night in \"Sex Against\nSex,\" the Lake Charles Press has the\nfollowing indicative of the success of\nthe company in that Ixniisiana town,\nboth In a histrionic as well as a social\nway;\nDie Ina Lehr Stock company closed\ntheir season's engagement at the\nLyric theater on Sunday. May 31, with\n\u201cTrue Irish Hearts\u201d as a farewell\nbill, which was immensely enjoyed by\nthe large, audience assembled. The\nPlayers were literally showered witn\nbouquets and souvenirs as tokens of\nappreciation of the work done by this\nclever company after their seven\nmonths\u2019 stay in this city and at the\nreception held after the play on the\nstoge. many tears were shed and It\nwas like the parting of relatives, as\nMiss Lehr and her company have\nmade many friends during their stay\nhere, and all wished them God-speed\non their joruuey westward.\nThe Lehr company left last nigh\u2019\nat 7:30 for San Antonio. Tex., to open\nup the big air dome and it is safe tn\npredict that the entire company will\nsoon become favorites in the Alamo\ncity.\nThe company was entertained Mon\nday night and Tuesday at the resi\ndence of Mi;s. J. C. Stout, one of Miss\nLehr\u2019s staunchest friends, and to say\nthat they were entertained royally by\nthis good woman and her worthy fam-\nMiss Ina Lehr Leadme .lady of the\nIna Dramatic company which\nwill open the Big Tent Theater Air\ndome Sudnay night in \u201cSex Against\nSex.\"\nily would be putting It mildly, as\nthey spared nothing, and exerted\nevery effort to make the company hap\npy before leaving.\nSongs, music and games were in\ndulged in right up until the last car\nleaving the house in time to carry\nthem to the dei\u00abt. where a sad good\nbye was said all around, and the most\npopular repertoire stock company\nthat ever played in Lake Charles were\non their way to the land of Davy\nCrockett and comrades.\nElectric Park.\nMcLane's family of trained dogs.\nMnrvo, the jail-breaker.\nNewton C. Bassett, the beautiful\nvoiced baritone ringer\nEarl and Fannie McLaine, sensa\ntional flying trapeze act.\nThe Electroscope.\nAn entirely new bill will be pre\nsented at the Electric Park theater\nopening tonight and will continue dur\ning the entire week. Several new\nand notable features will be pres\nented.\nMarvo, thej jail-breaker, has been\nengaged for another week at a large\n\u25a0alary. His marvelous feats of free\ning lilmself from hand-cuffs, straight\njackets and other shackles, whten\nhave been the marvel of officers of\nthree continents, will be repeated He\nwill also add a number of new tricks,\nIncluding an escape from a large\nwooden box In which hr will be\nnailed by a committee of stranger*\nand he will get out of a large paper\nbag which has been sealed after his\nentrance, without tearing the paper\nin anv way.\nMcLaine's troupe of trained dogs\nwill be the source of special pleasure\nfor the little folks. These dogs do a\nnumber of very clever tricks\nNewton C. Bassett, the baritone\nsinger, will render a number of selec\ntions.\nThe flying McLanes will be seen\nin their aerial act, their daring per\nformances on the trapeze, swing rings\nand other acts.\nThe electroscope will present the\nlatest pictures, the performance be\ning changed three times a week.\nThe Lyric.\nThe new bill that opens at the\nLyric tonight is acknowledged even\nbv the vaudeville performers that\nhave presented this the last\nfour weeks to be the strongest show\nthat has ever played the Lyric circuit\nThe nlll consists of the Four Ben\nninxtons in a novelty singing and\ndancing act with electrical effects. An\nelectrical fountain Is used which\nmakes the act very beautiful. Miss\nFisher, soubrette. does a clever sing\ning and dancing act. The other team\nis the Fishers, contortionists. Miss\nFisher Is acknowledged to be among\nthe greatest contortionists in the\nworld This week's show is very\nspectacular and musical. The show\nwill be closed with the Lyricscope.\nHave Outing.\nThe children of Temple Beth El\nwith their parents will have an outing\nall day today at Hot Wel.s.\n===n if IT\u2019S FROM KRESS\u2019, IT\u2019S BEST\nOne ne\nDay H Day\nOnly L Only\nP\nWINNING COMPETITIVE PURCHASE\n32987 YARDS OF GENUINE SWISS\nEMBROIDERY 7\nWe place on sale tomorrow morning at 9 o\u2019clock what the Kress\u2019 New York buyers\ndeclared was without doubt the greatest value offered in Rea! Swiss Embroidery.\nSo standing is the quality that we cannot promise it will last longer that One Day.\nIt is made in the good old fashioned way\u2019by the best skilled embroidery workers\nof Arbon, Switzerland, and is 36 to 45 inches wide. They are of newest exquisite\ndesigns and fit to adorn the most fashionable gown.\nIt is worth without contradiction $l.OO per yard (regular value) and 98c \u2014other\npeople\u2019s bargains. We offer you this great value tomorrow only.\nA Limited Quantity x Af i/arrl A Limited Quantity\nTo a Customer AiJC I lie ycAlCl Jo a Customer\nTAKE YOUR PURCHASE TO AN EMBROIDERY EXPERT, IF HE DOES NOT THINK IT THE\nGREATEST VALUE YOU EVER BOUGHT IN EMBROIDERY. BRING IT BACK,\n\u201cWATCH KRESS\u2019 WINDOWS\u201d\nHIS SCALP ON\nLYON\u2019S BELT\nMajor Mose Harris Is Deposed\nas Internal Revenue\nCollector.\nCecil Lyon has done it.\nHe snapped his fingers like the\ngrand vizier in the fairy book and oft\nwent Maj. Mose Harris' official head.\nCecil said he could.\nMaj. Mose dared him to try.\nPresto! Swish! off falls the ma\njor's noggin.\nHere\u2019s the elvdence of it:\n\"Internal Revenue service. Third\ndistrict of Texas, collector\u2019s office,\nAustin, June 1, 1908. \u2014-Mr. M C. Har\nris, deputy collector, San Anton\u2019c,\nTexas.\u2014Dear Sir. You are notified\nthat your separation from the service\nof the government as deputy collector\nof Internal revenue is effective from\nthis day (June I. 1908).\n\"You will please turn over to the\nlocal deputy at Su>* Antonio all pa\npers and government property you\nmay have, taking nls receipt In du\nplicate for same, transmitting the\ncopy to this office and retaining the\nother, respectfully,\n\u2019\u2019WEBSTER FLANAGAN,\n\u201cCollectcr.\u201d\nMaj. Harris didn't bat an eye when\nhe read this polite communication. He\nbought a return ticket to Chicago, in\ncluding sleeper coupons, gathered up\nthe papers in his contest of the dele\ngation from Texas, and hied himself\nto the Windy City by the lake.\nBut before going he took his trusty\npen in hand and wrote a few lines,\nusing the letter as a text. These few\nlines appear in the major\u2019s paper\n\"The Texas Republic\" which was is\nsued today. The major use< a special\nbrand of ink in which vitriol is a lead\ning Ingredient. Among other things\nhe says:\n\"A few weeks ago, at Fort Worth,\nthe editor of The Republic was as\nsured by Col. J-yon that at the snap\nof hia (Lyon\u2019s) finger.\u2019 the editor\u2019s\nbead would fall Into the basket. A\ncourteous and emphatic Invitation was\nextended him to lose no time in snap\ntping it, if he so desired to do.\n\"Evidently, he promptly acted on\nthe suggestion, for a peremptory or\nder Immediately followed from Hon.\nGeo. B. Cortelyou. aecretary of the\ntreasury, and Hon. John G. Caples\ncommissioner of internal revenue, di\nrecting the severance of The Repub\nlic's editor from the service.\"\nUNCLE SAM CLAIMS LAND.\nWashington\u2014Legal proceedings will\nbe instituted by the government to\ndispossess the Southern Pacific of\nland in western Oregon valued alt\n$35,000,000 and to obtain a decree an\nnulling the road's grant and restoring\nthe lands to the public domain. The\nlands In question were given to the\nold Southern Pacific many yeamago\nto encourage railroad construction.\nThe roads were built but it Is claimed\nthat other stipulations were not lived\nup to.\nYour stomach needs it and your\ngeneral health will be greatly\nimproved by it, as it prevents\nHeartburn, Sour Risings, Indi\ngestion, Costiveness, KidneA\nTroubles, Female Ills and\nMalaria.\nTHE GOSPEL OF GOOD CHEER\nBy E. C. Simmons, Chairman of ths Executive Committee of the National\nProsperity Association of St. Louis.\nWe have formed a business organization to be called the National Pros\nperity Association of St. Louis, having for les object the encouragement of a\nreturn of prosperity sooner than might otherwise occur without help, or\nwithout some active efforts on the part of the business men. We believe\nthat present conditions are exceedingly favorable to this. The bodv\u2014 com\nmercial\u2014has been very ill, and in a sense has had typhoid fever, but now\nthe fever has entirely left \u2014the disease is out. and the patient only remains\nsick and weak, so that permanent recovery is only a matter of time. How to\nqi'icken that recovery 1n a healthy manner is the problem we are undertak\ning, and we believe In the power of encouragement\u2014by showing to the world\nat large that conditions are fundamentally sound and healthy, and that uoth\nl-.g now exists but a lack of confidence to restore us to a full measure of\nprosperity such as existed a year ago. We are making an effort through the\npress and through other business associations and through the traveling\nsalesmen, to encourage the people to see the sunshine that is clearly in the\npathway, and to believe that things are very much better than most people\nthink thev are, and that with the present crop prospects soon to be realized,\nI* nothing unforeseen occurs in the immediate future, it is only a question ot\na very short time until the dinner paile will again be full and the unemployed\nwill again be employed at fair wages, and that there will be no reduction In\nwages of those already employed. We believe there is a great change of sen\ntiment with the intelligent people of the United States, and that It le Increas\ning very rapidly. It therefore seems to us to be a propitious time to do what\nwe can to encourage a quick return of prosperity, to the great benefit of the\nlaboring man and to the benefit ot all business interests.\nOn all sides we find expressions of favorable sentiments to the effect that\nfurther legislation against railroads and large corporations shall cease, that\nthe business Interests of this country shall be given a rest and that the de\npartments of justice may be allowed to proceed with their work In a quiet\nmanner, which, of course. Is greatly to be desired. It is absolutely essentl*!\nto the welfare of this country that the railroads should again prosper, because\nmore than one and a half million men are in the employ of the railroaas to\nd>y, and as many more are dependent upon their revenue from railrond in\nveitmepts, hence It is deemed almost impossible that we should return to a\nfull measure of prosperity excepting the railroads participate in the same.\nWith the full co-operation of the press of the United States\u2014which we\nnope to have \u2014and with the united efforts of the business associations u\u00ab all\nthe large cities, we feel confident of our ability to accelerate the speed of re\nturning prosperity- to a great degree. It is hardly necessary to say that every\nbody would like to have wages maintained at the highest figure, and without\n3 cut. There is no doubt as to the wisdom of this course. We are moat\nheartily in favor of It and are working to that end\u2014giving our time and\nmoney to accentuate better conditions and returning prosperity. We hope\nand expect -to have the co-operation of manufacturers. merchants, bankers,\nrailroads and the labor element\u2014in fact, every business interest of the\nUnited States. We ask every business man \u2014and. in fact, every commercial\nman and house in this country\u2014to lend us their aid\u2014to work with us\u2014to\nydn hands in the gospel of good cheer, and scatter seeds of sunshine in the\n-,n\u2019hs of all whom they meet. If they are pessimists, we want them to be\ncome optimists; If they are optimists, we want them to increase their opti\nmism- we want them to hunt for the sunshine; we want them to be cneerful\nIf their manner and in their conversations\u2014in their predictions\u2014in their\nhopes and aspirations.\nFundamentally, even-thing is all right\u2014the basis of our prosper!.v comes\nfrom the soil, and the products of the soil have never had greater value than\nat present. The outlook for crops is marvelously promising. To illustrate\u2014\nthe winter wheat crop\u2014-which is the first one of Importance that comes to our\nnotice \u2014is better than ever before in the history of this country. Kansas re\nports a condition of 105 on winter wheat\u2014something heretofore unknown.\nWhen the lumber Interests shut down, and the railroads laid off a lot of their\nemployes a large proportion of them went Immediately to the farmers, or\nplanters \u2019so that these tillers of the soil have, for the first time in many\nrears had enough labor to put in a full or large crop\u2014perhaps a larger crop\nthan ever before, and the planting is still going on. With a larger planting\nthan line ever gone into the ground, and with favorable weather It seems\nreasonable to suppose that we may have most excellent crops this year\u2014it\n\u2019ooks exceedingly probable. Therefore, everything which is the base ot our\nprosperity is right\u2014all that Is necessary now Is to restore confidence\u2014so\nthat the wheels of commerce begin to move again with the same rapidity\nhat thev did a rear or two ago. when we were at the height of our prosper\nity. and from which we went In a wonderfully short time to a very low stage\nof depression and hard times.\nWe ask the co-operation of everybody in the United States in this move\nment\u2014which we think has great merit, and which has great possibilities.\nAs to the French \u201cNobility.\"\n(Louisville* Courier-Journal.)\n\"Prince\" Helle de Sagan is a noble\nman of the republic of France, which\nis something like being the Earl of\nPawtucket or the Grand Duke ot Kala\nmazoo, and a good deal more unsub\nstantial than being a titled S-'mlnole\nof the Florida everglades or a royal\nYuma Indian of the cactus country,\nfor the nobility of the uncivilized\ntribes of American Indians at least\nrests upon the popular recognition\nwithin the tribe, while the people of\nJust\nThink!\n5 5 years\nas a house\nhold rem\nedy is the\nrecord back\nof the\nBitters.\nDon\u2019t you\nthink it de\nserves a\ntrial today?\nThe Real Elixir of Life\nDistilled water has a beneficial effect ou health and is the means\nof nutting new life into a rundown system. It is the real elixir of\nHfe\u2014 vitalizing and invigorating, because it absorbs impurities which\naffect and p\u00bb\u00ab v \u00abnt the human o-gansm from performing Ite proper\nfunctions.\nMono-Hydride\nDrinking Water.\u201d\n1s nure in the highest degree. By double distillation, all mineral and\nvegetable matters salts lime and disease germ? are effectually rs\nmoved\u2014made, absolutely pure The constant use of \"Mono-Hydrlde\u201d\nIs the sures' and safest health Insurance.\nCase rf 6 half-gallon bottles. 50c.\nG. A. Duerler Mfg. Co.\nFrance repudiated the nobility somo\ntime ago. And yet the noble Hede ds\nSagan says that his rank prevents hinx\nfrom working for a living.\nThe late Jay Gould was a somewhat\nunscrupulous exponent of frenzied\nfinance, but he was at least a man.\nIf he were alive today he would doubt\nless regard getting first a count ot\nthe republic of France and then a\nprince whose titles are read In a dead\nlanguage, and who are too noble to\nearn a living, a penalty sufficiently\nheavy to fit his crimes.\n11","height":"26488","width":"20532"}}
